snippet: Militia members using antiaircraft weapons, rocket-propelled grenades and light arms engaged Sunday in some of the heaviest clashes in months in Tripoli.
abstract: Khalif Heftar, retired Libyan general, claims responsibility for deadly attack on Parliament building in Tripoli; action came two days after Heftar's irregular force launched attack aimed at eradicating powerful Islamist militias from the eastern city of Benghazi.

byline.original: By SULIMAN ALI ZWAY and KAREEM FAHIM
byline.contributor: Suliman Ali Zway reported from Tripoli, and Kareem Fahim from Istanbul.

lead_paragraph: Militia members using antiaircraft weapons, rocket-propelled grenades and light arms engaged Sunday in some of the heaviest clashes in months in Tripoli.

headline.main: Ex-General Claims Responsibility for Libyan Parliament Attack
